result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: of Plea & Sentencing Hearing on 02-23-15 - (original filed in 14CM407)

Defendant Georgia D Germunson in court with attorney Anne Renc. David R. Knaapen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
14CM407 ct 1:  W/H Sentence: 3 yrs Probation: Maintain absolute sobriety with regards to alcohol and illegal drugs.  Continue to comply with AODA treatment recommendations. Maintain fulltime employment. Pay fine+costs.
14CM515 ct 1:  "
14CM516 ct 1:  "
14CM550 ct 1:  "
14CM556 ct 1:  "
14CM551, 14CM554, and 15CM1 to be DRI.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
 
14CM407 ct 1:   No Contest
14CM515 ct 1:   No Contest
14CM516 ct 1:   No Contest
14CM550 ct 1:   No Contest
14CM556 ct 1:   No Contest

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty 14CM407 ct 1, 14CM515 ct 1, 14CM516 ct 1, 14CM550 ct 1 and 14CM556 ct 1.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
 14CM551, 14CM554, and 15CM1 are Dismissed and Read In.

ADA Cousins makes sentencing arguments to the Court and request W/H Sentences. 
Atty Renc concurs with the joint recommendation.
Defendant makes statements to the Court. 

BY THE COURT: *************PROBATION**********
14CM407 ct 1:  W/H Sentence: 3 yrs Probation: 
Conditions:
Maintain absolute sobriety with regards to alcohol and illegal drugs.
Do not possess or consume alcohol or be on premises where alcohol is served/sold as its primary business except within scope of your employment.  
Do not possess/consume controlled substances without a valid prescription and be taken according to the prescription. 
Do not possess any drug paraphernalia. 
Obtain and maintain full-time employment or be enrolled in and attend school full time, or a combination of both resulting in full time.
Continue to comply with AODA treatment recommendations. 
Pay costs and DNA surcharge.
No pretrial incarceration credit.
Early discharge if compliant.

14CM515 ct 1:   W/H Sentence: 3 yrs Probation, concurrent:  Comply with same conditions 14CM407. Pay court costs.
14CM516 ct 1:   W/H Sentence: 3 yrs Probation, concurrent:  Comply with same conditions 14CM407. Pay court costs.
14CM550 ct 1:   W/H Sentence: 3 yrs Probation, concurrent:  Comply with same conditions 14CM407. Pay court costs.
14CM556 ct 1:   W/H Sentence: 3 yrs Probation, concurrent:  Comply with same conditions 14CM407. Pay court costs.

Any bond will be applied.
Plea hearing on February 23, 2015 at 11:00 am.
Pre-trial conference on February 9, 2015 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Georgia D Germunson in court with attorney Anne Renc. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  
Attorney/Defendant received copy of criminal complaint.
Court informs defendant of charges and maximum penalties.
Attorney/Defendant waives reading of complaint.

NOT GUILTY plea entered.

Atty Constable recommends a $2,500 signature bond with conditions as stated.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for February 9, 2015 at 10:00 am.
